Package: BooteJTKr
Type: Package
Title: Bootstrapped Empirical JTK_CYCLE for Rhythm Detection
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Vadim", "Vasilyev", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "you@example.com")
Description: A pure-R reimplementation of BooteJTK, a bootstrapped expansion of
    the empirical JTK_CYCLE (eJTK) method for detecting rhythmic signals in
    time-series data. Time series are parametrically bootstrapped from
    per-time-point means and standard deviations; each resampled ordering is
    matched against a bank of reference waveforms via Kendall's tau-b, and the
    bootstrap-weighted distributions of tau, phase, period and nadir are
    summarised. P-values are assigned from a gamma fit to a Gaussian null and an
    empirical null. The method is described in Hutchison et al. (2015)
    <doi:10.1371/journal.pcbi.1004094> and the BooteJTK preprint. The core
    engine uses only base R; an optional limma/voom + vash variance-shrinkage
    backend is provided but not required.
